operations center.

31:50.442 --> 31:56.782 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The superintendent is another
TEPCO veteran,
Akira Ono, on duty here since
June of 2013.

31:56.815 --> 32:01.286 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
AKIRA ONO, TEPCO (through
translator): Ever
since the disaster, we have been
working here

32:01.319 --> 32:08.059 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
24 hours a day 365 days a year.
We're ready
to respond to anything that
happens.

32:08.093 --> 32:15.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: His biggest
problem is water,
a steady torrent of radioactive
water. When

32:15.433 --> 32:21.006 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
rain falls, it seeps into the
soil, and flows
toward the ocean.

32:21.039 --> 32:27.112 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The earthquake on March 11,
2011, created
numerous breaches in the
basements of the

32:27.145 --> 32:34.553 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
reactor buildings. The
groundwater is contaminated
after it mixes with water that
is continuously

32:34.586 --> 32:42.661 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
pumped onto the damaged reactor
cores; 100,000
gallons of newly tainted water
is created

32:42.694 --> 32:45.864 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
here each and every day.

32:45.897 --> 32:51.570 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
They capture and pump most of it
into holding
tanks, lots of tanks. They build
one about

32:51.603 --> 32:58.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
every other day. A plateau above
the destroyed
reactors is now a tank farm,
brimming with

32:58.910 --> 33:01.913 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
more than 1,000 of them.

33:01.947 --> 33:06.218 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But have they managed to stop
all the radioactive
water from leaking into the
ocean?

33:06.251 --> 33:10.488 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEN BUESSELER, Woods Hole
Oceanographic Institution:
What we're hoping to find is a
container full

33:10.522 --> 33:12.290 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
of water.

33:12.324 --> 33:15.126 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: In this lab at
the Woods Hole
Oceanographic Institution, they
have been

33:15.160 --> 33:19.064 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tracking radioactive water from
Fukushima
since the accident.

33:19.097 --> 33:24.269 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEN BUESSELER: The level is
still measurable
and quite elevated, but it's not
anywhere

33:24.302 --> 33:26.371 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
near what it was at the peak of
the accident.

33:26.404 --> 33:31.977 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: Oceanographer Ken
Buesseler
says readings in April of 2011
showed cesium

33:32.010 --> 33:35.747 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
levels 50 million times higher
than normal
at the plant.

33:35.780 --> 33:40.318 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
KEN BUESSELER: The numbers
dropped very quickly,
but they also didn't go down to
zero. They

33:40.352 --> 33:43.889 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
didn't go to the background as
quick as you
would expect if they had stopped
the leaks.

33:43.922 --> 33:49.995 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: They hope to stop
the toxic
leaks by building a barrier.
They have encircled

33:50.028 --> 33:56.668 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the damaged reactors with 1,500
pipes that
go 100-feet deep. They will be
filled with

33:56.701 --> 34:03.074 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
coolant. The goal? Deep-freeze
the soil, creating
a mile-long water barrier.

34:03.108 --> 34:09.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The technique has long been used
in construction
to build tunnels. But can it
work at this

34:09.147 --> 34:12.350 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
scale for years and years?

