39:00.738 --> 39:01.372 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Syrian Voices.

39:01.406 --> 39:03.208 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Jeffrey Brown has our look.

39:03.241 --> 39:07.879 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A horror story
told in one
minute, that's the idea behind
"Fade to Black,"

39:07.912 --> 39:15.119 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
a short film by Amer Albarzawi,
who shows
us what's happened in Syria
through the changing

39:15.153 --> 39:20.191 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
image of Farah Brisly, an
actress from Damascus
who now lives in Istanbul.

39:20.225 --> 39:32.237 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's just one of the ways Syrian
artists have
responded to the destruction in
their country.

39:32.270 --> 39:36.407 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
In a refugee camp in Lebanon,
Farah's sister,
Diala, has found another,
working with Syrian

39:36.441 --> 39:42.814 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
children to design and painting
murals with
them to bring some color and joy
to their

39:42.847 --> 39:43.948 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
lives.

39:43.982 --> 39:47.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Diala spoke to us by Skype from
her home in
Beirut.

39:47.885 --> 39:56.761 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIALA BRISLY, Lebanon: Most of
them, they
skip school for two or three
years. And they

39:56.794 --> 40:03.534 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
had to work in the farms to help
their families.
So, they have really very, very
serious life

40:03.568 --> 40:06.070 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that doesn't belong to a
childhood, you know?

40:06.104 --> 40:11.042 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: The work on the
murals, she
says, begins with a
brainstorming session

40:11.075 --> 40:15.480 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as she asks them to imagine what
seems impossible,
like flying.

40:15.513 --> 40:23.988 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DIALA BRISLY: I tell them, like,
you can use
your imagination. It isn't
supposed to be

40:24.022 --> 40:25.757 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
realistic. You can imagine
anything.

40:25.790 --> 40:30.795 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Some of them, they think of
butterflies, of
birds, of air balloons, things
like this.

40:30.828 --> 40:36.834 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, after that, I take this
illustration and
I get inspired by it, and I
start designing

40:36.868 --> 40:41.372 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the mural. And the day after,
